### Test LLM Endpoint - Make sure your backend AND LLM server are running first!
### You can use this with VS Code REST Client extension or tools like Postman

@baseUrl = http://localhost:5290

### ========================================
### DUMMY DATA TESTS (No Database Required)
### ========================================

### Test 1 (Dummy): Default query with dummy data
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/test/llm-dummy
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "query": "How can I cut down on expenses and save more?"
}

### Test 2 (Dummy): Custom query with dummy data
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/test/llm-dummy
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "query": "What are my biggest spending categories and how can I reduce them?"
}

### Test 3 (Dummy): Specific month with dummy data
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/test/llm-dummy
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "query": "Analyze my spending and give me advice",
  "month": 1,
  "year": 2024
}

### ========================================
### REAL DATA TESTS (Requires Database)
### ========================================

### Test 1 (Real): Default query (current month)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/test/llm
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "query": "How can I cut down on expenses and save more?"
}

### Test 2: Custom query with current month
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/test/llm
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "query": "What are my biggest spending categories and how can I reduce them?"
}

### Test 3: Query for specific month (January 2024)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/test/llm
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "query": "How can I cut down on expenses and save more?",
  "month": 1,
  "year": 2024
}

### Test 4: Query for specific month (November 2024)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/test/llm
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "query": "Analyze my spending patterns and give me personalized advice.",
  "month": 11,
  "year": 2024
}

### Test 5: Get raw spending data (without LLM query)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/llm/spending-data?month=11&year=2024
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_FIREBASE_TOKEN_HERE

### ========================================
### NOTES
### ========================================
### - /api/test/llm-dummy: Uses hardcoded dummy data (NO database needed)
### - /api/test/llm: Uses real data from first user in database (requires data)
### - /api/llm/query: Production endpoint (requires Firebase authentication)
### - /api/llm/spending-data: Get raw spending data (requires Firebase authentication)

